{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JoLrzFo3NBpuwiCjXWc1zA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the ingress is created and the backends are showing the 3 Elasticsearch pod IPs. Let me wait a moment and then verify the setup by testing both HTTP and HTTPS access through the ingress-nginx controller.\n\nThe ingress-nginx controller service is a LoadBalancer type with ports 80 and 443. Since we're in a kind cluster, the external IP will likely be pending. I'll need to test using the NodePort or the pod's IP directly.\n\nLet me find the node port and test from inside the cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":381,"cache_read_input_tokens":32718,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":381},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c52a44e-2167-4e07-879c-5ec3483a2266","uuid":"cbfed280-503b-45ea-9509-cff3f4554bcd","request_id":"req_011CcRF5qRrgj6vVj7ecXSvu"}
